HEADWORD: Nonoic
<hw>No*no"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, derived from, or resembling, nonane; <as>as,
<ex>nonoic</ex> acid, which is also called <ex>pelargonic</ex>
acid</as>. Cf. <er>Pelargonic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
